<dl id="n05163d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05163d">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05163d"> 163(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> uniform garment Judas passes</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">15. Afterwards Judas said to the attendants, Let us provide for ourselves <mark>uniform garments</mark>, so that no one may be able to know our master. <br>16. This device pleased them, and they carried it out. <small> G.W. Foote and J.M. Wheeler, eds., <a name="SEPH" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SEPH"><cite title="source">The Jewish Life of Christ</cite></a>, (1879) 29</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
